WEBVTT

00:02.043 --> 00:04.045
(woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A.)

00:06.013 --> 00:07.248
I think it's broken.

00:07.248 --> 00:08.449
It's not broken.

00:08.449 --> 00:09.917
It might be broken.

00:09.917 --> 00:11.486
Do you want it
to be broken?

00:11.486 --> 00:14.188
No.

00:14.188 --> 00:15.890
But, I mean,
if it was broken,

00:15.890 --> 00:17.091
that would be very cool.

00:17.091 --> 00:19.227
I mean,

00:19.227 --> 00:20.595
"man breaks wife's shoulder

00:20.595 --> 00:22.563
from intense
lovemaking session"?

00:22.563 --> 00:25.199
(sighs)
This did not happen from sex.

00:25.199 --> 00:26.968
True or false:
we had great sex on Sunday.

00:26.968 --> 00:28.336
That was three days ago.

00:29.537 --> 00:31.038
Aftershocks.

00:31.038 --> 00:33.508
DOCTOR:
<i>What happened, exactly?</i>

00:33.508 --> 00:35.410
I really don't understand it.
I wasn't doing anything.

00:35.410 --> 00:37.478
I wasn't exercising,
I wasn't lifting anything.

00:37.478 --> 00:39.213
It's just so weird.

00:39.213 --> 00:42.150
An injury like this is normal
for someone your age.

00:42.150 --> 00:43.484
My age?

00:43.484 --> 00:46.187
I'm not even 40 yet.

00:46.187 --> 00:47.555
Oh. When do you turn 40?

00:47.555 --> 00:50.091
Tomorrow.

00:50.091 --> 00:52.193
RUSS:
If I may...

00:52.193 --> 00:54.896
isn't it possible
I boned her too hard?

00:57.465 --> 00:59.400
Just, like,
medically speaking?

01:05.473 --> 01:09.844
JESS: <i>Now that you've given her</i>
<i>the gift of a sexual injury,</i>

01:09.844 --> 01:13.114
what could you possibly
get her for her birthday?

01:13.114 --> 01:16.083
Oh, I think we'll just
do dinner with the kids.

01:16.083 --> 01:18.486
You know? Maybe, like,
a cake from Ralphs.

01:18.486 --> 01:20.054
Mm.

01:20.054 --> 01:21.255
Slow down.

01:21.255 --> 01:23.191
A cake from Ralphs? Wow.

01:23.191 --> 01:25.359
We don't make a big deal
out of birthdays.
Well, fine,

01:25.359 --> 01:27.161
but it's her 40th.
You need to bring it.

01:27.161 --> 01:29.564
I did. I did.

01:29.564 --> 01:30.965
Check it out.

01:32.500 --> 01:34.268
Uh-oh. You don't know
what "bringing it" means.

01:34.268 --> 01:35.503
What is this?

01:35.503 --> 01:38.272
Movie tickets
from our first date.

01:38.272 --> 01:40.007
Aw... that's...

01:40.007 --> 01:41.309
cute.
Yeah.

01:41.309 --> 01:42.610
Yeah. Cute isn't a
present though.

01:42.610 --> 01:44.011
Where's the real gift?

01:44.011 --> 01:45.947
Oh, give me a break.

01:45.947 --> 01:48.216
Not everybody needs fancy gifts,
you know?

01:48.216 --> 01:50.518
Like diamonds and... an island.

01:50.518 --> 01:51.919
Framed <i>Sister Act</i>
tickets

01:51.919 --> 01:53.254
or an island are
the only two gifts

01:53.254 --> 01:54.555
you can even think of

01:54.555 --> 01:56.457
for the most important
person in your life?

01:56.457 --> 01:58.059
It feels like
that's all there is.

01:58.059 --> 02:00.061
What's wrong
with you?
A lot.

02:00.061 --> 02:01.262
There's a lot
wrong with me.

02:01.262 --> 02:02.964
It started
at an early age.

02:02.964 --> 02:04.232
Oh, wow.
Here we go.

02:04.232 --> 02:06.000
No, my mother's...
No, tell me.

02:06.000 --> 02:07.869
my mother's 40th...
Mm-hmm.

02:07.869 --> 02:10.171
I took my allowance
and bought her

02:10.171 --> 02:12.206
a pair of earrings
from the drugstore.
Mm-hmm.

02:12.206 --> 02:13.541
And she said to me,

02:13.541 --> 02:15.142
"Oh, sweetie,
I would never wear those."

02:15.142 --> 02:18.479
Lina would totally wear
drugstore earrings.

02:18.479 --> 02:19.881
That's why I love her.

02:19.881 --> 02:21.082
That's nice.

02:21.082 --> 02:22.116
See?

02:22.116 --> 02:23.417
I would murder someone

02:23.417 --> 02:25.086
if they gave me
drugstore earrings.

02:25.086 --> 02:26.220
(chuckles):
Nice.

02:26.220 --> 02:27.321
Yeah.
Literally.

02:29.924 --> 02:30.958
(inhales sharply)

02:30.958 --> 02:32.360
Ow.

02:35.029 --> 02:36.330
Kenny?

02:36.330 --> 02:38.332
Your handwriting
looks weird.

02:38.332 --> 02:40.101
That's rude.

02:40.101 --> 02:42.136
Can't wait till
our real teacher comes back.

02:42.136 --> 02:44.405
That makes two of us.

02:44.405 --> 02:46.874
(school bell ringing)

02:46.874 --> 02:48.876
(children talking, laughing)

02:50.511 --> 02:52.880
Hey, there.

02:52.880 --> 02:55.116
You look so professional.
Oh, hi.

02:55.116 --> 02:56.484
How's subbing going?

02:56.484 --> 02:58.386
Oh, you know,

02:58.386 --> 03:00.321
I love one kid.
I like three.

03:00.321 --> 03:01.489
(quietly):
I hate 12.

03:01.489 --> 03:03.057
At least
you're working.
Yeah.

03:03.057 --> 03:05.059
I haven't had a
real job since 9/11.

03:05.059 --> 03:07.295
Anyway, I saw that
you have a birthday.

03:07.295 --> 03:09.463
It's on Facebook.

03:09.463 --> 03:11.098
That's great.

03:11.098 --> 03:12.433
Um, guess I'm not
invited to the party.

03:12.433 --> 03:14.068
But that's fine.
Oh. We're not...

03:14.068 --> 03:15.903
we're not, um,
having, like, a...

03:15.903 --> 03:17.605
No, it's okay. 'Cause
who wants a divorced lady

03:17.605 --> 03:19.440
at their party,
anyway? On the prowl,

03:19.440 --> 03:21.342
