each other?

12:41.752 --> 12:43.754
Oh, shit.

12:43.754 --> 12:46.690
I really am blowing this.

12:46.690 --> 12:48.659
Um, I forgot to tell you

12:48.659 --> 12:50.594
that we're using a
new sitter tonight.

12:50.594 --> 12:52.663
Why? What happened
to, um, Jordan?

12:52.663 --> 12:55.432
Oh, Jordan's just
coming to my party.

12:55.432 --> 12:56.500
She's fun.

12:56.500 --> 12:57.735
She jumps in pools.
(scoffs)

12:57.735 --> 12:59.470
Yeah, of course
she jumps into pools.

12:59.470 --> 13:01.038
She's, like, 20.

13:01.038 --> 13:02.740
Age is just a number.

13:02.740 --> 13:05.142
Are you okay?

13:05.142 --> 13:06.977
I'm fine.

13:08.312 --> 13:10.614
Jay thinks I'm under review.
Is that true?

13:10.614 --> 13:13.384
Is our relationship
under review?

13:13.384 --> 13:15.319
What?

13:15.319 --> 13:17.655
When did you talk to Jay?

13:17.655 --> 13:20.491
I don't know. Stacy had me bring
him some boxes for the party.

13:20.491 --> 13:22.726
Why are you getting
involved with the party?

13:22.726 --> 13:24.595
Because I'm the husband.

13:24.595 --> 13:26.530
Remember my 30th?
Forget your 30th.

13:26.530 --> 13:29.199
Okay? Your 40th is
going to rock.

13:29.199 --> 13:30.334
Hmm.

13:30.334 --> 13:31.702
<i>(doorbell rings)</i>

13:35.372 --> 13:38.042
Sorry, guys, can you just
give me a few minutes?

13:38.042 --> 13:39.282
Is everything okay?

13:39.282 --> 13:41.223
Party's off!
You know what?

13:41.223 --> 13:43.258
I'm the one who's gonna
say if the party's off!

13:43.258 --> 13:44.993
JAY: Shut up.
STACY: I didn't...

13:44.993 --> 13:46.727
Forget about your 40th.
(Jay and Stacy continue arguing)

13:46.727 --> 13:49.196
50th, now that's gonna rock.

13:56.353 --> 13:57.577
STACY:
<i>Well, he already ruined it.</i>

13:57.577 --> 13:59.569
Just like he ruins everything!

13:59.569 --> 14:01.971
There's got to be a way
to figure this out, right?

14:01.971 --> 14:03.440
Yeah, I'm excited
about my party.

14:03.440 --> 14:05.408
I'm really sorry.
He's on the spectrum.

14:05.408 --> 14:07.210
No, I have no
official diagnosis.

14:07.210 --> 14:08.611
That's just the
menopause talking.

14:08.611 --> 14:10.680
I'm as dry as you make me.
You know what?

14:10.680 --> 14:13.049
I think we're all as dry
as we make each other.

14:13.049 --> 14:15.685
LINA (whispering):
Why did you have to tell him
about the party?

14:15.685 --> 14:17.220
I didn't know it was a secret.

14:17.220 --> 14:19.389
There was scotch.
Oh, this is my 30th

14:19.389 --> 14:21.124
all over again.
It's fine, okay? It's fine.

14:21.124 --> 14:22.659
No, it's not!
You have to fix it.
I got it.

14:22.659 --> 14:24.060
I got it. Jay? Jay?

14:24.060 --> 14:25.128
What is going on here?

14:25.128 --> 14:26.262
This is my house!

14:26.262 --> 14:27.364
I understand that,
okay, but this is

14:27.364 --> 14:28.365
super important to Lina.

14:28.365 --> 14:29.532
Remember?

14:29.532 --> 14:30.734
I'm under review? Tenure?

14:30.734 --> 14:32.669
We talked about that.
I-I... yup.

14:32.669 --> 14:34.437
And I'm not going anywhere until
she gives me Stonewall Jackson.

14:34.437 --> 14:36.406
I don't have
your stupid toy!

14:36.406 --> 14:37.674
What-what toy?

14:37.674 --> 14:39.275
He collects miniatures.

14:39.275 --> 14:40.977
I hand-paint them.
The detail is exquisite.

14:40.977 --> 14:42.212
Thank you.
I will say that.

14:42.212 --> 14:43.213
They're beautifully made.

14:43.213 --> 14:45.715
Spectrum!
Menopause.

14:45.715 --> 14:47.650
Don't you think that any man
that paints little tiny

14:47.650 --> 14:50.086
army men is
on the autism spectrum?

14:50.086 --> 14:52.155
Don't you think that
any woman who hides

14:52.155 --> 14:55.325
exquisitely crafted figurines
is on the menopause spectrum?

14:55.325 --> 14:57.394
RUSS: Okay, well, how about
tonight we're all on the same

14:57.394 --> 14:59.396
spectrum, right? We're on,
like, the party spectrum.

14:59.396 --> 15:01.364
Yeah!
We're in the zone,
we're having fun.

15:01.364 --> 15:02.599
Party spectrum.
We got people
having a good time.

15:02.599 --> 15:04.033
We have...
(Lina gasps)

15:04.033 --> 15:06.069
I didn't take your racist toy!

15:06.069 --> 15:08.004
Okay, will you testify to that
under oath, hand to the Bible?

15:08.004 --> 15:09.439
(blows raspberry)
Didn't think so.

15:09.439 --> 15:11.207
See?
Ugh! I have to take a pill.

15:11.207 --> 15:13.243
Please, you already took one.
I'm gonna have more!

15:13.243 --> 15:14.744
Oh, um...
I'm really sorry
about the party.

15:14.744 --> 15:16.446
No, no, no. Stacy, wait!
Oh, it's no use!

15:16.446 --> 15:18.214
She's already gone, leave her.
Come here, Banjo!

15:18.214 --> 15:19.249
Just... come here.
(Banjo barks)

15:19.249 --> 15:21.017
(gasps)
Banjo, good boy.

15:21.017 --> 15:22.252
I'm gonna take him for a walk.

15:22.252 --> 15:24.087
She probably fed him Stonewall.

15:24.087 --> 15:26.055
I bet that's what happened
to Genghis Khan. Come on.

15:26.055 --> 15:27.757
STACY: I didn't
touch Genghis Khan!

15:27.757 --> 15:29.225
JAY: Yeah, this time
I'm gonna have evidence.

15:29.225 --> 15:31.761
Yeah, go get your hands
real dirty in there.

15:31.761 --> 15:33.129
Spectrum!

15:33.129 --> 15:35.265
Menopause!
(yells)

15:35.265 --> 15:37.500
(door closes)

15:37.500 --> 15:40.703
Well... guess
I'll just call Jordan

15:40.703 --> 15:42.505
and tell her the party's off.
No.

15:42.505 --> 15:44.474
It was stupid
to invite her anyway.

15:44.474 --> 15:47.243
No, no. We can still
pull this off, okay?
No.

15:47.243 --> 15:48.678
Parties are stupid.
We don't have to advertise

15:48.678 --> 15:50.547
our happiness;
we're happy enough.

15:50.547 --> 15:52.348
We are not happy enough.

15:52.348 --> 15:53.583
We are definitely not.

15:53.583 --> 15:55.051
We need more
happiness, okay?

15:55.051 --> 15:56.352
So here's the deal.

15:56.352 --> 15:58.588
I will handle Jay and
get him out of here,

15:58.588 --> 16:00.256
and you clean up Stacy.

16:00.256 --> 16:01.291
It's over, Russ.

16:01.291 --> 16:02.559
It's never over, okay?

16:02.559 --> 16:04.561
We can still do
this. Come on.

16:04.561 --> 16:05.695
Come on.

16:05.695 --> 16:07.764
Stacy?

16:07.764 --> 16:09.632
Come on, buddy, you can do it,
you can do it.

16:09.632 --> 16:11.601
Look, man, I get it.

16:11.601 --> 16:13.403
Like, I know
this is your house, okay?

16:13.403 --> 16:16.306
And you're having issues
with your lady, but...

16:16.306 --> 16:18.541
I could really use
a win tonight, you know?

16:18.541 --> 16:21.010
So... if there's
any way you could...

16:21.010 --> 16:23.680
I don't know, maybe just, like,
take off for a bit or whatever,

16:23.680 --> 16:25.114
like, that would be really cool.

16:25.114 --> 16:26.316
No, I'm not going anywhere

16:26.316 --> 16:27.750
until Banjo does his business.
Fine.

16:27.750 --> 16:29.385
How long does that take?

16:29.385 --> 16:32.055
Stacy sings to him
every time she walks him.

16:32.055 --> 16:33.590
So that's the only
way he'll go now.

16:33.590 --> 16:35.592
She sings to him?

16:35.592 --> 16:38.561
♪ Banjo... ♪

16:38.561 --> 16:43.433
♪ Banjo, time to go, Banjo. ♪

16:43.433 --> 16:46.703
Are you sure that that's
a good idea? 'Cause, um...

16:46.703 --> 16:48.671
Oh, it's not as
many as it seems.

16:48.671 --> 16:51.608
Over time, you build
up an immunity.

16:54.644 --> 16:58.114
BOTH:
♪ Banjo, Banjo ♪

16:58.114 --> 17:01.317
♪ Time to go, Banjo. ♪

17:01.317 --> 17:04.087
Stacy? What are you doing?

17:04.087 --> 17:05.688
Are you okay?

17:05.688 --> 17:09.225
How come I never wear this?

17:09.225 --> 17:10.693
(humming)

17:10.693 --> 17:13.096
(cell phone ringing)

17:13.096 --> 17:14.531
RUSS:
Hey, how's it going?

17:14.531 --> 17:17.267
Things are not good here.

17:17.267 --> 17:19.335
Um... oh, okay!

17:19.335 --> 17:20.737
Hey, good news!

17:20.737 --> 17:22.705
They found the general!
(doorbell rings)

17:22.705 --> 17:25.208
(gasps)
That must be your friends.

17:28.077 --> 17:30.613
Huh.
I guess we're early.

17:30.613 --> 17:32.682
Yeah.
Where is everybody?

17:32.682 --> 17:36.252
Hey, did they, uh, tell
you to bring the cake?

17:36.252 --> 17:38.321
They didn't have to.
It's a backup cake.

17:38.321 --> 17:39.722
Hello?

17:39.722 --> 17:41.624
It's a backup cake?

17:41.624 --> 17:44.394
Just in case I don't get
any of the main cake.

17:44.394 --> 17:47.096
I'm not dating or partying.
Cake is all I have left.

17:47.096 --> 17:48.264
Oh.
STACY:
Hello!

17:48.264 --> 17:50.033
AJ:
Hi.

17:50.033 --> 17:53.136
Did the Evite say
to wear ski attire?

17:53.136 --> 17:54.571
Hey! Hi, hi, hi, guys!
Say something...

17:54.571 --> 17:55.705
AJ:
Oh, there she is!

17:55.705 --> 17:59.342
The birthday girl and, uh...

17:59.342 --> 18:00.710
This is Stacy.
This is my friend.

18:00.710 --> 18:02.278
She's the hostess. (gasps) Hi.
(door opens)

18:02.278 --> 18:05.748
Lina, Lina,
I'm-I'm very excited,

18:05.748 --> 18:08.217
but, uh, but confused.
STACY: Come on in...

18:08.217 --> 18:10.320
Yeah.
...to my extravagant home.

18:10.320 --> 18:12.589
Okay, why don't you guys
just, uh, head into the...

18:12.589 --> 18:14.057
the kitchen?
Right in through...
The bedroom.

18:14.057 --> 18:16.125
No. In through here.
Kitchen.

18:16.125 --> 18:19.262
(indistinct chatter)

18:19.262 --> 18:21.731
Is she gonna be
all right?

18:21.731 --> 18:23.566
Who knows?

18:23.566 --> 18:25.068
What kind of pills
were they exactly?

18:25.068 --> 18:26.436
Oh, they were white ones.

18:26.436 --> 18:28.338
Maybe they were
orange ones.

18:28.338 --> 18:29.372
(gasps)

18:29.372 --> 18:32.241
Maybe it was candy corn.

18:32.241 --> 18:34.243
Who does this?!
LINA: Oh, my God.

18:34.243 --> 18:36.045
No respect
for our country's history.

18:36.045 --> 18:37.981
Is that... dog shit?

18:37.981 --> 18:40.183
His name is Jay.

18:40.183 --> 18:41.985
You should be tried for treason.

18:41.985 --> 18:45.455
You should be tried
for animal... husbandry.

18:45.455 --> 18:47.056
Okay, guys, the
party. Let's...

18:47.056 --> 18:49.225
Why do you care?
You weren't even on the Evite.

18:49.225 --> 18:51.294
He should've thrown
the party himself.
Well, maybe he would've

18:51.294 --> 18:53.630
thrown the party if she laughed
at his jokes once in a while.

18:53.630 --> 18:55.231
This guy is hilarious.

18:55.231 --> 18:57.033
Hey, I laugh
at your jokes, right?

18:57.033 --> 18:58.635
You say, "That's funny."
It's just...

18:58.635 --> 19:00.370
it's not really
the same thing, you know?

19:00.370 --> 19:02.171
JORDAN:
Lina?
Jordan!

19:02.171 --> 19:03.606
Oh.
(chuckles)

19:03.606 --> 19:05.241
Jordan?
Hi, Jordan!
Who's Jordan?

19:05.241 --> 19:07.143
Who isn't Jordan?
The babysitter

19:07.143 --> 19:08.177
that Lina's obsessed with.
I don't care.

19:08.177 --> 19:10.413
Hey! Hey, girl!

19:10.413 --> 19:13.049
Happy birthday.
Thank you.

19:13.049 --> 19:14.517
Let me get you a drink.
We have, um....
Oh...

19:14.517 --> 19:15.652
You know what? Just take mine.

19:15.652 --> 19:17.353
(chuckles)
Gosh, um...

19:17.353 --> 19:20.023
I wish I could, but, uh,
I actually can't stay.

19:20.023 --> 19:21.658
Oh, no.

19:21.658 --> 19:24.060
I-I know.
I had this other thing.

19:24.060 --> 19:28.097
But I really just wanted
to stop by, 'cause, like, wow!

19:28.097 --> 19:29.465
You know, you're 40!

19:29.465 --> 19:31.234
I know.

19:31.234 --> 19:33.970
It's so weird.

19:33.970 --> 19:35.638
(laughs)

19:35.638 --> 19:37.273
So, um...

19:37.273 --> 19:39.008
I'll-I'll talk to you soon?

19:39.008 --> 19:40.209
Yeah.

19:40.209 --> 19:41.444
Totally.

19:41.444 --> 19:43.446
Happy birthday.
Thanks.

19:43.446 --> 19:45.281
It's great.

19:45.281 --> 19:46.616
Bye.

19:51.020 --> 19:53.656
(indistinct chatter)

19:53.656 --> 19:55.758
Hey.

19:55.758 --> 19:56.993
There you are.

19:56.993 --> 19:58.995
What's going on?

20:01.097 --> 20:02.632
We should go.

20:02.632 --> 20:05.101
Why?

20:05.101 --> 20:08.471
All our friends
are old and ugly.

20:08.471 --> 20:10.306
So are we.

20:10.306 --> 20:13.109
No, this is, like, a...
this is a cool party.

20:13.109 --> 20:14.210
Is it?

20:14.210 --> 20:15.244
Yeah.

20:18.414 --> 20:20.083
I mean, it's okay.

20:25.054 --> 20:27.023
It's about to get better.

20:28.257 --> 20:29.492
(whoops)

20:33.029 --> 20:34.230
(laughing)

20:35.431 --> 20:36.466
(laughs)

20:36.466 --> 20:38.401
See? I can still

20:38.401 --> 20:39.669
make you laugh.

20:39.669 --> 20:41.237
How's the water?
It's freezing.

20:41.237 --> 20:42.672
It's so cold.

20:42.672 --> 20:44.607
Oh, my God, it's terrible.

20:44.607 --> 20:46.476
Oh, my God!

20:46.476 --> 20:47.610
It's an awesome party now!

20:47.610 --> 20:49.345
(gasps)

20:49.345 --> 20:51.514
(crowd cheering)
RUSS: Yeah!

20:51.514 --> 20:52.648
It's so freezing!

20:52.648 --> 20:53.750
I know, right?

20:53.750 --> 20:56.219
(laughing)

20:56.219 --> 20:57.653
(grunts)

21:02.325 --> 21:04.160
RUSS:
<i>Not a bad party, right?</i>

21:04.160 --> 21:06.362
It was better than my 30th.
Mm-hmm.

21:06.362 --> 21:07.530
I like to keep the bar low.

21:07.530 --> 21:08.664
That's your move.

21:08.664 --> 21:10.633
(laughs)
I know.

21:10.633 --> 21:14.070
Oh, hey, this is from AJ.

21:14.070 --> 21:15.238
Oh, that's sweet.

21:15.238 --> 21:17.573
Mm-hmm.

21:26.449 --> 21:28.718
I don't understand.

21:28.718 --> 21:33.256
Me neither.
